  ],

  "important_notes": [
    "DDTrace\\Tracer is the core implementation; uses internal C-extension functions (dd_trace_*, active_span(), root_span(), etc.)",
    "GlobalTracer is the entry-point 'factory' for the DDTrace legacy API (not a TracerFactory class per se)",
    "TracerFactory and TracerProvider are OTel SDK concepts; in this codebase TracerSharedState (OTel SDK) connects the Tracer to SpanProcessors and Samplers",
    "InstrumentationScope (OTel) = identifies the library that created spans (name, version); exposed via Span::getInstrumentationScope()",
    "OpenTracer\\Tracer::make() is the designated factory method for the OpenTracing adapter",
    "flush() sends spans to Datadog Agent via Transport::send(); recommended at request end via register_shutdown_function or fastcgi_finish_request",
    "Priority sampling flows: Tracer sets sampling priority on root span context and propagates via inject/extract",
    "Distributed tracing: on construction, Tracer reads current_context() for distributed_tracing_parent_id/origin"
  ],

